{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S4zTRgcb1Lp3fnejLxohn3","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Ralph Project Specification: AGS Notification Center\n     2→\n     3→## Global Goal\n     4→When this loop completes, AGS should be the sole notification daemon — receiving, displaying (toast popups + center panel), and managing all desktop notifications within the Chrysaki design system, with swaync fully removed.\n     5→\n     6→## Product Overview\n     7→A native notification center for the AGS Wayland shell that replaces swaync. It provides toast popups for incoming notifications, a toggleable history panel, do-not-disturb mode, and an unread badge on the bar icon — all styled to Chrysaki's jewel-toned chamfered aesthetic.\n     8→\n     9→## Target Audience\n    10→Desktop power user running a Hyprland/Wayland desktop who needs unified notification management within the Chrysaki design system instead of a disconnected external daemon.\n    11→\n    12→## Feature Scope\n    13→\n    14→### Must-Have (MVP)\n    15→- **AstalNotifd integration**: AGS registers as the D-Bus notification daemon, replacing swaync — acceptance: `notify-send` test notification appears in AGS, not swaync\n    16→- **Notification center panel**: Layer-shell popup (top-right, below bar) showing notification history — acceptance: panel toggles on NotificationToggle click, shows all received notifications in reverse chronological order\n    17→- **Toast popups**: Incoming notifications show a brief auto-dismissing toast (top-right, ~5s) — acceptance: toast appears on `notify-send`, fades after ~5s, stacks max 3-4 with overflow queued\n    18→- **Dismiss individual**: Each notification has a dismiss/close button — acceptance: clicking dismiss removes notification from list\n    19→- **Clear all**: Button to dismiss all notifications at once — acceptance: clears list, shows empty state\n    20→- **Do-not-disturb toggle**: Suppresses toast popups while still accumulating in the center — acceptance: with DND on, `notify-send` adds to center but no toast appears\n    21→- **Chrysaki styling**: Chamfered island container, jewel tone accents, glassmorphism background — acceptance: visually matches existing bar panels (ServicePanel pattern)\n    22→- **Unread badge**: NotificationToggle icon shows unread count — acceptance: badge appears when >0 unread, disappears when center opened or cleared\n    23→\n    24→### Should-Have\n    25→- **Notification actions**: Render action buttons from the notification (e.g., \"Reply\", \"Open\") — acceptance: action buttons visible, clicking fires the D-Bus action callback\n    26→- **Notification body markup**: Render HTML body content (bold, links, images) — acceptance: rich notifications from apps render formatted text\n    27→\n    28→### Nice-to-Have\n    29→- **Notification urgency styling**: Critical notifications get Error red accent — acceptance: critical notifications visually distinct\n    30→- **Scroll overflow**: Panel scrolls when notification count exceeds visible area\n    31→\n    32→## Technical Architecture\n    33→- **Stack**: TypeScript/JSX (AGS 2 / Astal), SCSS, GTK4 layer-shell\n    34→- **Components**: `NotificationCenter.tsx` (panel), `NotificationToast.tsx` (popups), `NotificationToggle.tsx` (bar button + badge), `_notifications.scss` (styles)\n    35→- **Key Integrations**: AstalNotifd (D-Bus notification daemon), GLib.timeout_add (toast auto-dismiss), existing ChamferedIsland/ServicePanel pattern\n    36→\n    37→## Technical Constraints\n    38→- swaync must not be running when AGS claims D-Bus notification ownership — document removal in README\n    39→- Toast stacking capped at 3-4 visible; overflow must be queued, not dropped\n    40→- AstalNotifd API usage should follow the same Astal patterns already proven with AstalNetwork/AstalBattery\n    41→\n    42→## Project Status\n    43→- **Overall Status**: COUNCIL_PENDING\n    44→- **Current Iteration**: 