{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GRr8ZEtNCue5mzwYaG3Hs2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import app from \"ags/gtk4/app\"\n     2→import { Astal } from \"ags/gtk4\"\n     3→import AstalNotifd from \"gi://AstalNotifd\"\n     4→import GLib from \"gi://GLib\"\n     5→import { notifd } from \"./NotificationCenter\"\n     6→\n     7→const MAX_VISIBLE = 4\n     8→const TOAST_MS = 5000\n     9→\n    10→// Module-level state: visible toast array, overflow queue, widget refs\n    11→let _container: any = null\n    12→let _window: any = null\n    13→let _visible: AstalNotifd.Notification[] = []\n    14→let _queue: AstalNotifd.Notification[] = []\n    15→const _rowWidgets: Map<number, any> = new Map()\n    16→\n    17→function updateWindowVisibility(): void {\n    18→  if (_window) _window.visible = _visible.length > 0\n    19→}\n    20→\n    21→function buildToastRow(n: AstalNotifd.Notification): any {\n    22→  const isCritical = n.urgency === AstalNotifd.Urgency.CRITICAL\n    23→  return (\n    24→    <box\n    25→      class={`notif-toast-row${isCritical ? \" notif-toast-critical\" : \"\"}`}\n    26→      orientation={1}\n    27→      spacing={2}\n    28→    >\n    29→      <box class=\"notif-toast-header\" spacing={6}>\n    30→        <label\n    31→          class=\"notif-row-app\"\n    32→          label={n.appName || \"App\"}\n    33→          halign={1}\n    34→          hexpand\n    35→        />\n    36→        <button\n    37→          class=\"notif-dismiss-btn\"\n    38→          label=\"󰅖\"\n    39→          onClicked={() => removeToast(n)}\n    40→        />\n    41→      </box>\n    42→      <label\n    43→        class=\"notif-row-summary\"\n    44→        label={n.summary || \"\"}\n    45→        halign={1}\n    46→        xalign={0}\n    47→        wrap\n    48→      />\n    49→      {n.body && (\n    50→        <label\n    51→          class=\"notif-row-body\"\n    52→          label={n.body}\n    53→          halign={1}\n    54→          xalign={0}\n    55→          wrap\n    56→          ellipsize={3}\n    57→        />\n    58→      )}\n    59→    </box>\n    60→  ) as any\n    61→}\n    62→\n    63→function addToastToContainer(n: AstalNotifd.Notification): void {\n    64→  if (!_container) return\n    65→  const row = buildToastRow(n)\n    66→  _rowWidgets.set(n.id, row)\n    67→  _container.append(row)\n    68→}\n    69→\n    70→function removeToastFromContainer(n: AstalNotifd.Notification): void {\n    71→  if (!_container) return\n    72→  const row = _rowWidgets.get(n.id)\n    73→  if (row) {\n    74→    _container.remove(row)\n    75→    _rowWidgets.delete(n.id)\n    76→  }\n    77→}\n    78→\n    79→// Promote queued toasts into visible slots\n    80→function pump(): void {\n    81→  while (_visible.length < MAX_VISIBLE && _queue.length > 0) {\n    82→    const next = _queue.shift()!\n    83→    _visible = [..._visible, next]\n    84→    addToastToContainer(next)\n    85→    scheduleAutoDismiss(next)\n    86→  }\n    87→  updateWindowVisibility()\n    88→}\n    89→\n    90→function scheduleAutoDismiss(n: AstalNotifd.Notification): void {\n    91→  GLib.timeout_add(GLib.PRIORITY_DEFAULT, TOAST_MS, () => {\n    92→    removeToast(n)\n    93→    return GLib.SOURCE_REMOVE\n    94→  })\n    95→}\n    96→\n    97→function removeToast(n: AstalNotifd.Notification): void {\n    98→  _visible = _visible.filter((v) => v !== n)\n    99→  removeToastFromContainer(n)\n   100→  pump()\n   101→}\n   102→\n   103→function enqueue(n: AstalNotifd.Notification): void {\n   104→  if (notifd.dontDisturb) return\n   105→  if (_visible.length < MAX_VISIBLE) {\n   106→    _visible = [..._visible, n]\n   107→    addToastToContainer(n)\n   108→    scheduleAutoDismiss(n)\n   109→    updateWindowVisibility()\n   110→  } else {\n   111→    _queue.push(n)\n   112→  }\n   113→}\n   114→\n   115→notifd.connect(\"notified\", (_self: unknown, id: number) => {\n   116→  const n = notifd.get_notification(id)\n   117→  if (n) enqueue(n)\n   118→})\n   119→\n   120→notifd.connect(\"resolved\", (_self: unknown, id: number) => {\n   121→  const inVisible = _visible.find((v) => v.id === id)\n   122→  if (inVisible) {\n   123→    _visible = _visible.filter((v) => v.id !== id)\n   124→    removeToastFromContainer(inVisible)\n   125→  }\n   126→  _queue = _queue.filter((v) => v.id !== id)\n   127→  pump()\n   128→})\n   129→\n   130→export function NotificationToast() {\n   131→  const { TOP, RIGHT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n   132→  return (\n   133→    <window\n   134→      namespace=\"chrysaki-notification-toast\"\n   135→      anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n   136→      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n   137→      marginTop={48}\n   138→      marginRight={8}\n   139→      visible={false}\n   140→      application={app}\n   141→      $={(win: any) => {\n   142→        _window = win\n   143→      }}\n   144→    >\n   145→      <box\n   146→        class=\"notif-toast-stack\"\n   147→        orientation={1}\n   148→        spacing={6}\n   149→        $={(box: any) => {\n   150→          _container = box\n   151→        }}\n   152→      />\n   153→    </window>\n   154→  )\n   155→}\n   156→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MmiFhQo5idvBT36BTDMSpC","session_id":"ed3ae5d5-6d68-4c01-8434-1b6218a239c4","uuid":"e49a3f47-b08a-4577-83fc-72bd7cac4038","timestamp":"2026-03-17T11:54:28.572Z"}
{"type":"system","subtype":"task_started","task_id":"a2b8398fb373ddfe0","tool_use_id":"toolu_018mvTpnic7V6befpCXUMmEE","description":"Read app.ts and style files","task_type":"local_agent","prompt":"Read the following files in full and return their complete contents:\n1. /home/kiriketsuki/dots/chrysaki-ralph-ags-notification-center/ags/.config/ags/app.ts\n2. /home/kiriketsuki/dots/chrysaki-ralph-ags-notification-center/ags/.config/ags/styles/_notifications.scss\n3. /home/kiriketsuki/dots/chrysaki-ralph-ags-notification-center/ags/.config/ags/styles/style.scss\n\nReturn the COMPLETE content of each file, verbatim.","uuid":"8af4cf8c-320a-4eff-86d7-5f4342a7f79a","session_id":"ed3ae5d5-6d68-4c01-8434-1b6218a239c4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NKxDZyh4KY5XisuhR6nDY8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import app from \"ags/gtk4/app\"\n     2→import { createBinding } from \"ags\"\n     3→import { Astal } from \"ags/gtk4\"\n     4→import AstalNotifd from \"gi://AstalNotifd\"\n     5→\n     6→const PANEL_NAME = \"chrysaki-notification-center\"\n     7→\n     8→export const notifd = AstalNotifd.get_default()!\n     9→\n    10→// --- Unread count (module-level state, no GObject needed) ---\n    11→\n    12→let _unreadCount = 0\n    13→const _unreadListeners: Array<() => void> = []\n    14→\n    15→function _setUnreadCount(n: number): void {\n    16→  _unreadCount = Math.max(0, n)\n    17→  _unreadListeners.forEach((cb) => cb())\n    18→}\n    19→\n    20→export function getUnreadCount(): number {\n    21→  return _unreadCount\n    22→}\n    23→\n    24→export function onUnreadChange(cb: () => void): void {\n    25→  _unreadListeners.push(cb)\n    26→}\n    27→\n    28→notifd.connect(\"notified\", () => {\n    29→  _setUnreadCount(_unreadCount + 1)\n    30→})\n    31→\n    32→// --- Panel toggle ---\n    33→\n    34→export function toggleNotificationCenter(): void {\n    35→  const panel = app.get_window(PANEL_NAME)\n    36→  if (panel) {\n    37→    if (!panel.visible) {\n    38→      _setUnreadCount(0)\n    39→    }\n    40→    panel.visible = !panel.visible\n    41→  }\n    42→}\n    43→\n    44→// --- Notification list helpers ---\n    45→\n    46→// Sanitize a freedesktop.org HTML notification body to safe Pango markup.\n    47→// The spec allows a small HTML subset (<b>, <i>, <u>, <a>, <img>, <br>).\n    48→// Pango supports <b>, <i>, <u>, <s>, <tt>, <span>, <sub>, <sup>, <big>, <small>.\n    49→// Returns the processed string and whether Pango markup mode should be enabled.\n    50→function sanitizeBodyMarkup(body: string): { markup: string; hasMarkup: boolean } {\n    51→  if (!/<[a-zA-Z]/.test(body)) {\n    52→    return { markup: body, hasMarkup: false }\n    53→  }\n    54→  const PANGO_SAFE = new Set([\n    55→    \"b\",\n    56→    \"i\",\n    57→    \"u\",\n    58→    \"s\",\n    59→    \"tt\",\n    60→    \"span\",\n    61→    \"sub\",\n    62→    \"sup\",\n    63→    \"big\",\n    64→    \"small\",\n    65→  ])\n    66→  const markup = body\n    67→    // <br> and <br/> → newline\n    68→    .replace(/<br\\s*\\/?>/gi, \"\\n\")\n    69→    // Strip <img> entirely (no visual equivalent in Pango)\n    70→    .replace(/<img\\b[^>]*>/gi, \"\")\n    71→    // Strip <a> open/close tags — keep link text, Pango has no href rendering\n    72→    .replace(/<a\\b[^>]*>/gi, \"\")\n    73→    .replace(/<\\/a>/gi, \"\")\n    74→    // Pass Pango-safe tags through; strip everything else\n    75→    .replace(\n    76→      /<\\/?\\s*([a-zA-Z][a-zA-Z0-9]*)(\\s[^>]*)?\\s*>/g,\n    77→      (match, tag: string) => (PANGO_SAFE.has(tag.toLowerCase()) ? match : \"\"),\n    78→    )\n    79→  return { markup, hasMarkup: true }\n    80→}\n    81→\n    82→function BodyLabel({ body }: { body: string }) {\n    83→  const { markup, hasMarkup } = sanitizeBodyMarkup(body)\n    84→  return (\n    85→    <label\n    86→      class=\"notif-row-body\"\n    87→      label={markup}\n    88→      useMarkup={hasMarkup}\n    89→      halign={1}\n    90→      xalign={0}\n    91→      wrap\n    92→      ellipsize={3}\n    93→    />\n    94→  )\n    95→}\n    96→\n    97→function formatTimestamp(unixTime: number): string {\n    98→  const nowSec = Math.floor(Date.now() / 1000)\n    99→  const diff = nowSec - unixTime\n   100→  if (diff < 60) return \"just now\"\n   101→  if (diff < 3600) return `${Math.floor(diff / 60)}m ago`\n   102→  if (diff < 86400) return `${Math.floor(diff / 3600)}h ago`\n   103→  return `${Math.floor(diff / 86400)}d ago`\n   104→}\n   105→\n   106→function NotificationRow(n: AstalNotifd.Notification) {\n   107→  const isCritical = n.urgency === AstalNotifd.Urgency.CRITICAL\n   108→  return (\n   109→    <box\n   110→      class={`notif-row${isCritical ? \" notif-row-critical\" : \"\"}`}\n   111→      orientation={1}\n   112→      spacing={2}\n   113→    >\n   114→      <box class=\"notif-row-header\" spacing={6}>\n   115→        <label\n   116→          class=\"notif-row-app\"\n   117→          label={n.appName || \"App\"}\n   118→          halign={1}\n   119→          hexpand\n   120→        />\n   121→        <label\n   122→          class=\"notif-row-time\"\n   123→          label={formatTimestamp(n.time)}\n   124→          halign={2}\n   125→        />\n   126→        <button\n   127→          class=\"notif-dismiss-btn\"\n   128→          label=\"󰅖\"\n   129→          onClicked={() => n.dismiss()}\n   130→        />\n   131→      </box>\n   132→      <label\n   133→        class=\"notif-row-summary\"\n   134→        label={n.summary || \"\"}\n   135→        halign={1}\n   136→        xalign={0}\n   137→        wrap\n   138→      />\n   139→      {n.body && <BodyLabel body={n.body} />}\n   140→      {n.actions.length > 0 && (\n   141→        <box class=\"notif-actions\" spacing={4}>\n   142→          {n.actions.map((action) => (\n   143→            <button\n   144→              class=\"notif-action-btn\"\n   145→              label={action.label}\n   146→              hexpand\n   147→              onClicked={() => n.invokeAction(action.id)}\n   148→            />\n   149→          ))}\n   150→        </box>\n   151→      )}\n   152→    </box>\n   153→  )\n   154→}\n   155→\n   156→// --- Clear-all button ---\n   157→\n   158→function ClearAllButton() {\n   159→  const notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\n   160→  return (\n   161→    <button\n   162→      class=\"notif-clear-all-btn\"\n   163→      label=\"󰆴  Clear all\"\n   164→      visible={notifications.as((list) => list.length > 0)}\n   165→      onClicked={() => {\n   166→        const list = [...notifd.notifications]\n   167→        list.forEach((n) => n.dismiss())\n   168→        _setUnreadCount(0)\n   169→      }}\n   170→    />\n   171→  )\n   172→}\n   173→\n   174→// --- DND toggle (header button) ---\n   175→\n   176→function DndToggle() {\n   177→  const dnd = createBinding(notifd, \"dontDisturb\")\n   178→  return (\n   179→    <button\n   180→      class={dnd.as((on) => `notif-dnd-btn${on ? \" notif-dnd-active\" : \"\"}`)}\n   181→      label={dnd.as((on) => (on ? \"󰂛\" : \"󰂚\"))}\n   182→      tooltipText={dnd.as((on) =>\n   183→        on ? \"DND on — click to disable\" : \"DND off — click to enable\",\n   184→      )}\n   185→      onClicked={() => {\n   186→        notifd.dontDisturb = !notifd.dontDisturb\n   187→      }}\n   188→    />\n   189→  )\n   190→}\n   191→\n   192→// --- Panel window ---\n   193→\n   194→export function NotificationCenter() {\n   195→  const { TOP, RIGHT } = Astal.WindowAnchor\n   196→  const notifications = createBinding(notifd, \"notifications\")\n   197→\n   198→  return (\n   199→    <window\n   200→      name={PANEL_NAME}\n   201→      namespace={PANEL_NAME}\n   202→      visible={false}\n   203→      anchor={TOP | RIGHT}\n   204→      exclusivity={Astal.Exclusivity.IGNORE}\n   205→      marginTop={48}\n   206→      marginRight={8}\n   207→      application={app}\n   208→    >\n   209→      <box class=\"notif-panel\" orientation={1} spacing={0}>\n   210→        <box class=\"notif-panel-header\" spacing={4}>\n   211→          <label\n   212→            class=\"notif-panel-title\"\n   213→            label=\"󰂚  Notifications\"\n   214→            halign={1}\n   215→            hexpand\n   216→          />\n   217→          <ClearAllButton />\n   218→          <DndToggle />\n   219→        </box>\n   220→        <box class=\"notif-panel-list\" orientation={1} spacing={4}>\n   221→          {notifications.as((list) =>\n   222→            list.length === 0\n   223→              ? [\n   224→                  <label\n   225→                    class=\"notif-empty\"\n   226→                    label=\"No notifications\"\n   227→                    halign={3}\n   228→                    valign={3}\n   229→                  />,\n   230→                ]\n   231→              : [...list].reverse().map((n) => NotificationRow(n)),\n   232→          )}\n   233→        </box>\n   234→      </box>\n   235→    </window>\n   236→  )\n   237→}\n   238→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MmiFhQo5idvBT36BTDMSpC","session_id":"ed3ae5d5-6d68-4c01-8434-1b6218a239c4","uuid":"abd571dc-34e6-40c4-a177-eade2e203f43","timestamp":"2026-03-17T11:54:28.735Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HLhekecsDBT2r3UkBZoF57","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { getUnreadCount, onUnreadChange, toggleNotificationCenter } from \"./NotificationCenter\"\n     2→\n     3→export function NotificationToggle() {\n     4→  return (\n     5→    <box class=\"notif-toggle-wrap\" valign={3}>\n     6→      <button\n     7→        class=\"utility-button\"\n     8→        label=\"󰂚\"\n     9→        onClicked={() => toggleNotificationCenter()}\n    10→        tooltipText=\"Toggle notifications\"\n    11→      />\n    12→      <label\n    13→        class=\"notif-badge\"\n    14→        visible={false}\n    15→        label=\"\"\n    16→        valign={1}\n    17→        $={(self: any) => {\n    18→          function update() {\n    19→            const count = getUnreadCount()\n    20→            if (count > 0) {\n    21→              self.label = count > 9 ? \"9+\" : String(count)\n    22→              self.visible = true\n    23→            } else {\n    24→              self.label = \"\"\n    25→              self.visible = false\n    26→            }\n    27→          }\n    28→          onUnreadChange(update)\n    29→        }}\n    30→      />\n    31→    </box>\n    32→  )\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MmiFhQo5idvBT36BTDMSpC","session_id":"ed3ae5d5-6d68-4c01-8434-1b6218a239c4","uuid":"b5421672-284c-4b2f-9c04-15f7b00328b2","timestamp":"2026-03-17T11:54:28.883Z"}
